OpenCC
------------------------------------------
Open Chinese Convert (OpenCC) is an opensource project for conversion between
Traditional Chinese and Simplified Chinese, supporting character-level
conversion, phrase-level conversion, variant conversion and regional idioms
among Mainland China, Taiwan and Hong kong.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.3-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libmarisa0-0.2.4-4
  libopencc-devel-1.1.6-1bl1
  libopencc1.1-1.1.6-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.39-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.35.5-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libmarisa-devel-0.2.4-4
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/BYVoid/OpenCC

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/BYVoid/OpenCC/archive/refs/tags/ver.1.1.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack OpenCC-1.1.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./OpenCC-1.1.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/OpenCC-1.1.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/OpenCC-1.1.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopencc1.1-1.1.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopencc-devel-1.1.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

